 in your field and maybe even make some new ones? Come join other seismology students at the Irish Bank for some drinks and free food. We'll have space reserved at the bar area inside. We hope to see you there! 2. New Facebook Page for Students in the AGU Seismology Section To keep up to date about the Seismology Student Mixer and other seismology student activities visit our Seismology Section Students Facebook page. Thanks to our new student representative, Caroline Eakin, for setting this up! 3. 2014 Elections for Seismology Section Officers Elections for the 2015&amp;ndash;2017 Seismology Section President-elect and Seismology Section Secretary will open in June 2014.&amp;nbsp; We are in the process of forming a nominations committee to choose two candidates for each office.&amp;nbsp; Please send your suggestions for candidates to Karen Fischer. 4. Seismology Section Web Editor We are looking for a web editor for the Seismology Section.&amp;nbsp; If you might be interested, please contact Karen Fischer for details.&amp;nbsp; Opportunities exist to engage with other section and focus group web editors and AGU staff at the Fall Meeting. Best regards, Karen Fischer, AGU Section President, Seismology Richard Allen, AGU Section Secretary, Seismology Greg Beroza, AGU Section President-elect, Seismology Peter Shearer AGU Section Past President, Seismology Caroline Eakin AGU Section Student Representative, Seismology</summary> 
